answerText: Biscayne Bay[10] The Venetian Causeway allows access to this major city in Dade County. The Calle (KA-yay) Ocho festival occurs annually in this city's Little Havana district.

question: Question: A national park named after this body of water includes a settlement of wooden houses on a sand bank known as Stiltsville.  [10] Name this popular snorkeling destination. A bridge called the Venetian Causeway crosses this bay, which was initially considered part of Everglades National Park
